  <!-- ============ UPGRADE ============ -->
  <section class="upgrade">
    <div class="upgrade-inner reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">Want Every Meal Handled Instead?</p>
      <h2>The Frozen Classic Meal — {usd(products.frozen_classic_4w.price)}</h2>
      <p>Three full meals, a dessert, and a daily healing drink, seven days a week — for the household where no one has time to cook at all.</p>
      <a href={route("/frozen-postpartum-meals/classic", 'en')} class="btn btn-primary">Explore the Frozen Classic Meal</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FAQ ============ -->
  <section class="faq-band" id="faq">
    <svg class="botan faq-botan" viewBox="0 0 200 200" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <g>
        <path d="M185 25 C165 60 140 88 112 108" stroke="#5E6B4F" stroke-width="1.8" fill="none" opacity="0.55"/>
        <ellipse cx="150" cy="62" rx="10" ry="16" fill="#5E6B4F" opacity="0.35" transform="rotate(30 150 62)"/>
        <ellipse cx="98" cy="118" rx="28" ry="34" fill="#D99FB0" opacity="0.5"/>
        <path d="M98 86 C111 94 117 108 113 122 C109 134 100 142 98 144 C96 142 87 134 83 122 C79 108 85 94 98 86Z" fill="#C77D7D" opacity="0.45"/>
        <circle cx="98" cy="118" r="9" fill="#E8C46A" opacity="0.75"/>
      </g>
    </svg>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <p class="eyebrow">Good Questions</p>
        <h2>Before you decide</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list reveal">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is frozen really as good as fresh?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>It's the same food from the same kitchen. Every dish is cooked fresh in our own Walnut, CA kitchen, then frozen to hold its nourishment until it reaches you. Thaw it in the refrigerator, heat it through, and it tastes the way it was cooked — warm and home-style, nothing like a supermarket TV dinner. Frozen is simply how we bring a real Zuo Yue Zi to families who live far from fresh delivery.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is this enough food on its own?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>This plan is designed to work alongside home cooking — it covers the slow-simmered soups, the recovery dishes, and the desserts, while breakfast, vegetables, and simple sides come from your own kitchen. If you need every meal handled, the Frozen Classic or Frozen Herbal plans cover the full day.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can I pair this with the herbal drinks?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes — it's one of the most common pairings. Add the herbal drinks at {usd(products.frozen_herbal_drink_7_1w.price)}/week with your shipments, or order the standalone Herbal Pack ({usd(products.herbal_drink_pack_30d.price)}), which was made for moms whose families are cooking for them.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Can my family eat the soups too?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The portions are made for one — the new mother. Many customers tell us their partner ends up sharing anyway, but if you want enough for two, the safer answer is a second portion. We'd rather be honest than have you run out three days in.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Will a month of frozen food fit in my freezer?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Longer plans ship weekly, so you're only ever storing about a week at a time. Many families keep five days in the freezer and let a couple of days thaw in the refrigerator. If space is truly tight, a small upright freezer is often enough — and it earns its keep long after the confinement month.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How do I reheat the meals?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Thaw overnight in the refrigerator, then reheat until it's piping hot all the way through — an internal temperature of 165°F (74°C) is the safe mark for reheated food. Each day arrives pre-portioned in its own pillow-size thermal bag, so there's no meal planning, no labels to decode, and nothing to assemble — grab one bag, that's your day.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>When should I order?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>At least one month before your due date, if you can. The week your baby arrives, you will not have the bandwidth to compare plans or fill out forms — and you shouldn't have to. Your shipments start when you tell us the baby has arrived, not on a fixed calendar.</p></div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

